# Permanent Mount of /dev/sda1 to /home/dspace_backup

## 1. Create Mount Directory
```bash
sudo mkdir -p /home/dspace_backup
```

## 2. Get the UUID of /dev/sda1
```bash
sudo blkid /dev/sda1
```

Example output:
```
UUID="46D7-609B" TYPE="vfat"
```

## 3. Unmount Auto-mounted Path
```bash
sudo umount /media/hp/46D7-609B
```
If busy:
```bash
sudo umount -l /media/hp/46D7-609B
```

## 4. Edit /etc/fstab to Add Permanent Mount
```bash
sudo nano /etc/fstab
```

Add:
```
UUID=46D7-609B  /home/dspace_backup  vfat  uid=1000,gid=1000,umask=000,auto,rw  0  0
```

## 5. Test the fstab Entry
```bash
sudo mount -a
```

## 6. Verify the Mount
```bash
df -h
```

## 7. Optional: Disable Auto-Mount
```bash
gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.media-handling automount false
gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.media-handling automount-open false
```

Unmount and remount:
```bash
sudo umount -l /media/hp/46D7-609B
sudo mount -a
```
